        <tr>

          <td width="90%" height="0" align="left" valign="top" class="style14">
            <table width="100%" border="0" align="right" cellpadding="0" cellspacing="0">
              <tr>
              	<td class="style14">
		  This book is about learning how to use R for
		  performing data mining.<br /><br />  The book follows
		  a "learn by doing it" approach to data mining
		  instead of the more frequent theoretical description
		  of the techniques available in this discipline.
		  This is accomplished by presenting a series of
		  illustrative case studies for which all necessary
		  steps, code and data are provided to the
		  reader. <br /><br /> The book writing style
		  establishes it as a good source for practical
		  classes on data mining, but also as an
		  attractive document to professionals working on data
		  mining in non-academic environments.<br /><br />  Most
		  of the main data mining processes and techniques are
		  covered in the book by means of the presentation of
		  four detailed case studies:

		  <ul type="square" class="style2">
		    <li class="style14">Predicting algae blooms</li>
		    <li class="style14">Predicting stock market returns</li>
		    <li class="style14">Detecting fraudulent transactions</li>
		    <li class="style14">Classifying microarray samples</li>
		  </ul>
		</td>
              </tr>
            </table>
          </td>

